<br>
First, Spirit of Oak give 10hp/tick.  I have tested and I am sure.<br>
<br>
Second, I am not sure how I am getting the 65hp/tick, but of that number I am certain.  Using your numbers (and my oak number) I should have:<br>
15 (tunic) + 15 (staff) + 4 (NS) + 15 (regrow) + 10 (oak) + 2 (sitting) = 61 hp/tick.<br>
I have tested staff and I know it is 15.  The 2 for sitting is just a guess since I see 63/tick and 2/tick lagging about a second or two behind.  I have read that the tunic is 17, so that brings me to 63.  I will have to test further to figure it out the other 2hp/tick.<br>
<br>
Third, I do not own ES legs, but I am guessing that they are not usable if NS or SLN is up.  Just like I don't think ES BP is usable if I have regrow up.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I do not know how much I get from pure medding, but I am now getting a 24.6 mana/tick bonus (3 from Oak + 21.6 from manastone conversion of 65hp) in old world.  At 60, I will have to trade off Oak for PotG since I hear they do not stack.  With Oak I have 6.3mana/tick (3 oak directly + 3.3 from 10hp conversion) and PotG has only 6mana/tick.  Not too bad, but I will be able to stack Mask (3 mana) with PotG (6 mana) for 9/tick.  It sure will be nice once I get a flowing thought item.<br>
<br>
Enough rambling<br>
<br>
